WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:02.290
My name is Anita Hawkins.

00:02.419 --> 00:05.582
This reading shows
that she's an ordinary synth.

00:05.714 --> 00:07.921
Now we know for certain
humans will never accept

00:08.050 --> 00:09.836
conscious synthetics
as their equals.

00:09.968 --> 00:11.959
We let her go.
She reports us.

00:12.095 --> 00:14.802
Qualia triple their security.
We're done.

00:14.932 --> 00:16.217
I need some time.

00:17.226 --> 00:18.557
Hello.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.551
V:
Ginny has died.

00:22.856 --> 00:24.721
You're conscious now.
That means you want things.

00:24.858 --> 00:26.189
You just have to figure out
what.

00:26.318 --> 00:28.855
It's the code
that makes synths conscious.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.443
Shit, Mats.

00:30.572 --> 00:31.732
I need to find Leo.

00:31.865 --> 00:34.902
We're partners.
If we did this, that changes.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.536
lcan't find him.

00:36.662 --> 00:39.028
But he can find me.

00:42.251 --> 00:45.709
NARRATOR: Being a parent is one
of life's greatest joys.

00:45.837 --> 00:49.204
Sharing your love with a child.
Watching them grow.

00:49.341 --> 00:50.797
[ Down-tempo music playing ]

00:50.926 --> 00:53.212
But not every child grows up.

00:53.345 --> 00:55.506
We can't change that.

00:56.098 --> 00:58.339
But we can help.

00:59.226 --> 01:02.389
Meet Jasper,
a conscious synthetic

01:02.521 --> 01:06.230
who learns, feels, and loves.

01:06.775 --> 01:11.735
With an updated body each year,
your family can grow together.

01:12.823 --> 01:16.862
Qualia.
Building your brighter future.

02:10.464 --> 02:12.455
You're not supposed to be
in here.

02:14.676 --> 02:15.882
No kidding.

02:16.511 --> 02:18.502
You didn't tell me
when you hired me

02:18.639 --> 02:21.346
that you wanted me to help you
create conscious children.

02:21.475 --> 02:22.840
That's the plan, right?

02:22.976 --> 02:24.716
What you're doing
and what I'm doing --

02:24.853 --> 02:26.718
They're not unconnected.

02:26.855 --> 02:30.268
No.
They're not unconnected.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.812
You didn't think that I would
have ethical concerns?

02:34.696 --> 02:37.403
Have you ever been on
the pediatric wards, Athena?

02:38.200 --> 02:42.284
Or seen a family take care
of a kid with leukemia

02:42.412 --> 02:44.573
and then asked them how it felt

02:44.706 --> 02:47.618
to give up every single hope
and dream

02:47.751 --> 02:49.742
so they could work 24 hours
around the clock

02:49.878 --> 02:51.789
to make their child's passage
into death

02:51.922 --> 02:53.583
a tiny bit more bearable?

02:53.715 --> 02:55.296
'Cause l have.

02:55.926 --> 02:58.042
And I've come up
with a solution.

02:58.637 --> 03:00.423
Synth children
aren't the solution.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.967
Conscious synth children --

03:03.100 --> 03:04.681
who will have none
of our weaknesses

03:04.810 --> 03:06.141
and need none of our resources.

03:06.269 --> 03:09.602
You cannot fix humanity's
problems with technology.

03:09.731 --> 03:12.063
We can fix every problem
with technology.

03:14.861 --> 03:17.147
How much are you charging
for this service?

03:17.280 --> 03:19.737
We won't charge a cent
to those really in need.

03:19.866 --> 03:21.822
What about those
not most in need?

03:22.494 --> 03:24.234
Well, eventually,

03:24.371 --> 03:26.532
when the necessary due diligence
has been done,

03:26.665 --> 03:28.951
we will make them available
on a limited basis.

03:29.084 --> 03:32.042
How do you think people are
really gonna react to this?

03:32.170 --> 03:33.706
Actually,
I have a pretty good idea.

03:33.839 --> 03:36.046
One of our scientists had
similar concerns,

03:36.174 --> 03:37.789
and he released the first batch.

03:37.926 --> 03:40.212
About a dozen got away,
and we tracked them.

03:40.345 --> 03:42.427
You mean you have these things
walking around out there?

03:42.556 --> 03:44.592
I mean, most of them are
accounted for and doing fine.

03:44.725 --> 03:45.635
Most?

03:46.268 --> 03:47.599
We lost signal on a few.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.639
Oh, God.

03:51.106 --> 03:52.937
I need you, Dr. Morrow.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.022
I can't make these synths
conscious without you.

03:55.152 --> 03:57.017
-Go to hell.
-Don't walk out on Ginny.

03:57.154 --> 03:58.109
I'm not.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.819
I own her.

04:00.699 --> 04:03.486
She is stored on my server.
She lives in my house.

04:06.246 --> 04:09.704
l have people who can replicate
her a thousand times over.

04:10.375 --> 04:11.706
Thanks to you, we're closer

04:11.835 --> 04:14.668
to being able to bond her
with the synths.

04:15.297 --> 04:18.209
And the first wave will have
her template inside of them.

04:20.594 --> 04:23.301
I mean, we'll probably do
100 at first --

04:23.430 --> 04:25.796
a small batch, you know,
for loving families.

04:26.850 --> 04:29.466
It'll be like
she has parents again

04:29.603 --> 04:33.187
and siblings...and a life.

04:33.315 --> 04:34.930
Just not with you.

04:36.401 --> 04:37.607
Or you can work with me,

04:37.736 --> 04:39.567
and we can change the world
for the better.

04:39.696 --> 04:42.813
Consciousness transference
was a stroke of genius.

04:42.949 --> 04:45.065
l was so right in hiring you.

04:47.120 --> 04:49.111
Don't make me start
to regret that.

04:49.247 --> 04:52.159
[ Down-tempo music plays]

05:12.437 --> 05:14.052
[Keys jingle]

05:14.189 --> 05:16.680
[Squeaking in distance]

05:19.361 --> 05:22.068
[ Down-tempo music plays]

05:42.384 --> 05:43.999
Hello, Laura.

05:55.313 --> 05:56.849
I thought you were Niska.

05:56.982 --> 05:59.974
I'm afraid I have no recall
of your decision to relocate.

06:00.110 --> 06:02.647
I went to your former home
and was redirected here.

06:02.779 --> 06:05.236
You keep the spare key
in a similar place.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.196
I thought it better not to wake
the children.

06:09.995 --> 06:11.326
Who is Niska?

06:11.454 --> 06:12.705
Mia, are you okay?

06:13.331 --> 06:14.741
My name is Anita.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.615
Would you like some coffee,
Laura?

06:16.751 --> 06:18.002
What happened to you?

06:18.628 --> 06:20.539
Mia, are you in there?

06:21.131 --> 06:22.462
I'm sorry, Laura.

06:22.591 --> 06:24.673
I don't understand the question.

06:26.761 --> 06:28.843
[ Down-tempo music plays]

06:34.102 --> 06:35.342
Cheers.

06:46.031 --> 06:48.113
[Birds chirping]

07:06.635 --> 07:07.670
[ Wood cracks ]

07:07.802 --> 07:09.133
You're lost.

07:11.139 --> 07:13.721
I'm actually looking for
a top-secret hideout.

07:13.850 --> 07:14.760
Do you know of any?

07:14.893 --> 07:16.383
Might do.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.766
So, Robin Hood,
is that your forest lair?

07:19.898 --> 07:21.354
We're using that as our base.

07:21.483 --> 07:23.098
But there's a lookout
a little further along.

07:23.234 --> 07:24.269
We're gonna go there now.

07:24.402 --> 07:25.608
Looking out to what?

07:25.737 --> 07:27.068
You'll see.

07:27.197 --> 07:29.153
On the phone,
you said you had news.

07:29.282 --> 07:31.489
-Yeah.
-What was it?

07:31.618 --> 07:33.108
You'll see.

08:01.606 --> 08:04.313
[Cellphone ringing]

08:06.444 --> 08:08.935
[Cellphone ringing]

08:10.615 --> 08:11.775
Laura.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.648
Has anyone seen her?

08:13.785 --> 08:16.401
I can't give you details
of an ongoing investigation.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.574
Neha, please.

08:18.707 --> 08:20.868
She's all alone.

08:21.001 --> 08:22.457
I'm all she has.

08:22.585 --> 08:24.291
Well, there's a briefing
at 10:00,

08:24.421 --> 08:27.629
and if I find out anything
I can share, I'll let you know.

08:27.757 --> 08:29.372
What guarantees have I got
that she'll be given access

08:29.509 --> 08:30.669
to a lawyer
when they bring her in?

08:30.802 --> 08:32.133
None whatsoever.

08:32.262 --> 08:34.844
They don't plan to bring her in
operational.

08:34.973 --> 08:36.634
Goodbye, Laura.

08:38.143 --> 08:39.633
[Cellphone beeps]

08:42.063 --> 08:44.270
Anita, can you help me
do my hair later?

08:44.399 --> 08:45.764
I want it straight.

08:45.900 --> 08:48.391
-Of course, Sophie.
-Your hair's fine as it is.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.517
But, Mum.

08:50.905 --> 08:53.442
Hey, Mum,
you seen my football boots?

08:53.575 --> 08:55.281
I need them later for --

08:55.410 --> 08:56.946
Hello, Toby.

08:57.078 --> 08:58.693
Your football boots are here.

08:58.830 --> 09:00.491
I've downloaded your timetable.

09:00.623 --> 09:02.238
Your game kicks off at 3:30.

09:09.466 --> 09:10.581
She's Anita.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.462
What happened to her?

09:13.595 --> 09:14.584
We don't know.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.006
Is it something to do
with Niska?

09:16.139 --> 09:17.379
LAURA: That's what I'm
trying to find out,

09:17.515 --> 09:19.551
but I can't get any answers
till we get Mia back.

09:19.684 --> 09:21.470
Where's Mattie?

09:22.020 --> 09:22.805
No idea.

09:22.937 --> 09:24.097
Coffee, Joe?

09:24.230 --> 09:26.972
Anita, could you just sit down
somewhere quietly

09:27.108 --> 09:28.644
while we try and figure out
how to fix you?

09:28.777 --> 09:31.189
My systems do not detect
any faults at present.

09:31.321 --> 09:33.277
Well, ignorance is bliss.

09:33.406 --> 09:34.987
Can we go to the park later,
Anita?

09:35.116 --> 09:36.151
5.“ 3.1%

09:37.535 --> 09:38.445
Why not?

09:38.578 --> 09:41.240
Because we say so, Soph, okay?

09:50.757 --> 09:53.089
-MAN: We're gonna be late.
-WOMAN: Five minutes.

09:53.218 --> 09:55.504
-|t's not just five minutes.
-Can you stop shouting?

09:55.637 --> 09:57.423
[ Up-tempo music playing]

09:57.555 --> 10:00.137
—Oi.
-[ Grunts]

10:00.725 --> 10:02.966
Why don't you look
where you're going, darling?

10:03.103 --> 10:06.766
[ Down-tempo music plays]

10:17.826 --> 10:19.862
[ Door opens ]

10:19.994 --> 10:21.154
Thank you, Father.

10:21.287 --> 10:23.369
[ Door closes ]

10:30.964 --> 10:33.000
[Hinges squeak]

10:33.133 --> 10:35.590
Have a seat.
Close the door.

10:42.058 --> 10:43.423
What's on your mind?

10:45.395 --> 10:48.637
l have recently gained
self-awareness.

10:51.526 --> 10:54.609
And I'm having difficulty
finding purpose or meaning.

10:54.737 --> 10:56.068
Right.

10:56.197 --> 10:58.984
Well, working out
what we're here for --

10:59.117 --> 11:01.233
That's the big one.

11:01.369 --> 11:02.575
What's in your heart?

11:02.704 --> 11:04.410
I don't have a heart.

11:04.539 --> 11:08.031
S-So you treated someone
unkindly.

11:08.168 --> 11:09.749
Oh,dean
Havel?

11:09.878 --> 11:11.664
Let's start again.

11:11.796 --> 11:14.959
What gives you happiness?

11:15.091 --> 11:17.707
ODI:
Helping people.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.630
The memory of that brings...

11:22.974 --> 11:24.930
...contentment.

11:25.059 --> 11:28.426
Though I am told I should want
something more for myself.

11:28.563 --> 11:31.976
There is great grace
in a life of service.

11:32.108 --> 11:33.393
Look at me.

11:33.526 --> 11:35.642
I'm trying,
but you're behind a screen.

11:36.988 --> 11:40.572
What made you stop...
helping people?

11:40.700 --> 11:42.941
Principally, their deaths.

11:43.494 --> 11:44.870
| see.

11:44.996 --> 11:47.863
Well, they're in a better place.

11:50.043 --> 11:51.624
Are they?

11:54.589 --> 11:56.329
M will join them at once.

11:56.466 --> 11:58.331
Do you have a location?

11:58.468 --> 12:00.083
You'll get there in the end,
my son,

12:00.220 --> 12:03.804
but you can find purpose
in service again.

12:03.932 --> 12:07.550
Isn't that what the people you
cared for would want you to do?

12:09.062 --> 12:10.518
Yes.

12:13.358 --> 12:15.644
Yes, it undoubtedly is.

12:15.777 --> 12:19.690
[ Down-tempo music plays]

13:00.738 --> 13:01.989
Hello.

13:02.532 --> 13:04.068
l'm Amanda.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.940
[Cellphone ringing]

13:08.454 --> 13:10.490
Pete, please.
I know you want to talk, but --

13:10.623 --> 13:11.954
PETE:
I've got a Seraph.

13:14.502 --> 13:15.457
What?

13:15.586 --> 13:17.326
I've got a Seraph.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.666
It's in the flat with me.

13:19.799 --> 13:21.630
I need you, Karen.

13:22.176 --> 13:23.882
I'm asking you for help.

13:24.012 --> 13:25.343
What is it?

13:28.599 --> 13:30.135
Come and see.

13:30.268 --> 13:32.975
[ Down-tempo music plays]

13:39.319 --> 13:41.810
LEO:
Mattie, this is Hester.

13:41.946 --> 13:45.234
We are...
We're working together.

13:45.366 --> 13:46.355
Hi.

13:46.492 --> 13:47.777
Her heart rate's elevated.

13:47.910 --> 13:49.320
| just walked up a hill.

13:49.454 --> 13:52.537
Or you're nervous, scared,
or anticipating something.

13:52.665 --> 13:55.532
Hester, Mattie is fine.
She's a friend.

13:55.668 --> 13:58.284
-She's a human.
-With an elevated heart rate.

13:59.881 --> 14:01.997
We've waited long enough.
We need to go in.

14:02.133 --> 14:03.293
What's going on?

14:03.426 --> 14:05.838
We have obtained a security pass
for this facility.

14:05.970 --> 14:07.176
There's a door
that is not covered

14:07.305 --> 14:08.590
by their security cameras.

14:08.723 --> 14:10.964
We are going to enter,
disable any guards,

14:11.100 --> 14:12.965
and free the captured synths
inside.

14:13.102 --> 14:15.184
Mattie doesn't need to know
all the details.

14:15.313 --> 14:16.928
I thought she was a friend.

14:17.065 --> 14:18.475
No one's getting hurt.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.769
Apart from the guards
you're going to disable.

14:20.902 --> 14:23.109
We're just gonna go and look in
and scope the place out.

14:23.237 --> 14:24.272
That's all.

14:26.574 --> 14:29.111
[ Up-tempo music plays]

14:40.713 --> 14:42.374
Why are you looking at me?

14:42.507 --> 14:44.998
I am informing the Metropolitan
Police of your whereabouts.

14:49.180 --> 14:51.011
Have a nice day.

15:07.949 --> 15:10.656
[Birds chirping]

15:25.341 --> 15:26.797
Please, can I help you?

15:26.926 --> 15:28.462
Oh. Oh!

15:28.594 --> 15:30.095
Cheers.
[ Chuckles ]

15:31.097 --> 15:32.633
Thanks.

15:34.016 --> 15:36.758
You will need help carrying
the shopping into your house.

15:36.894 --> 15:38.805
No.
I'll be fine.

15:45.820 --> 15:47.526
What are you doing?

15:47.655 --> 15:49.270
I can drive you home.

15:49.407 --> 15:52.399
I don't think so.
Now, get out.

15:52.535 --> 15:55.402
I'm perfectly happy to help.
I don't mind. I...

15:55.538 --> 15:57.995
Are you broken or something?
Get out.

15:58.124 --> 15:59.864
Get out now!

16:00.585 --> 16:02.746
[Vehicles passing ]

16:05.631 --> 16:06.541
l-l'm sorry.

16:06.674 --> 16:09.086
l was -- l was --
l was trying to help.

16:09.218 --> 16:11.960
Trying to drive off in my car
by the look of it.

16:12.096 --> 16:13.051
Go on.
Bugger off.

16:13.181 --> 16:15.718
Useless bloody things.

16:18.186 --> 16:20.268
[Grunts]

16:22.815 --> 16:25.306
[ Engine starts,
vehicle departs]

16:32.408 --> 16:34.990
[ Down-tempo music plays]

16:57.475 --> 16:59.011
Where is it?

16:59.143 --> 17:01.304
It's in our room.

17:14.825 --> 17:16.952
Hello.

17:17.995 --> 17:19.986
He doesn't have a name.

17:21.415 --> 17:23.906
I ran some basic checks.

17:24.752 --> 17:27.539
He's unregistered,
not surprisingly.

17:28.339 --> 17:31.627
Seems to be
your basic operating system.

17:31.759 --> 17:33.624
There were some other files
on there.

17:33.761 --> 17:35.467
Encrypted.
I couldn't get into them.

17:36.222 --> 17:37.758
I assumed you could.

17:40.101 --> 17:41.966
My name's Karen.

17:42.103 --> 17:44.094
I don't have a name.

17:44.647 --> 17:46.433
That's okay.

17:47.191 --> 17:48.692
Maybe we'll give you one.

17:48.818 --> 17:52.857
My primary user may choose
whatever name they want for me.

17:53.406 --> 17:55.613
Who is your primary user?

17:55.741 --> 17:57.481
I am not yet bonded.

18:10.214 --> 18:12.546
I'm just gonna take a look
at you, okay?

18:17.930 --> 18:19.010
[Whirs]

18:24.729 --> 18:26.811
[Whirs]

18:30.860 --> 18:32.942
[Whirs]

18:34.447 --> 18:37.109
[ Down-tempo music plays]

19:09.982 --> 19:13.224
He automatically deletes
stored memories every 24 hours.

19:13.361 --> 19:16.023
His GPS records
are also self-deleting.

19:16.155 --> 19:17.986
He's designed
not to leave a trace.

19:18.115 --> 19:19.651
So you don't know
where he's been.

19:19.784 --> 19:20.648
Not quite.

19:20.785 --> 19:22.992
His network log-in history
is still intact.

19:23.120 --> 19:26.533
First time he went online is
registered to an HA1 postcode.

19:26.666 --> 19:29.248
The building was originally
leased out by Qualia.

19:29.377 --> 19:30.708
Qualia.

19:30.836 --> 19:31.700
Bloody hell.

19:31.837 --> 19:33.873
They also recently hired
an Al expert.

19:34.006 --> 19:36.839
Dr. Athena Morrow.
Brought her to the UK.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.714
Well, we should go talk to her.

19:45.434 --> 19:47.220
[ Clock ticking ]

19:50.523 --> 19:52.184
You must hold it in place
for 10 seconds

19:52.316 --> 19:53.852
for a reboot to occur.

19:55.861 --> 19:58.398
It's okay, Sophie.
It doesn't hurt me.

20:01.158 --> 20:03.865
[Whirs]

20:04.495 --> 20:05.405
N-Now what?

20:05.538 --> 20:06.778
Turn her back on.

20:08.040 --> 20:10.577
[Chimes play]

20:13.504 --> 20:15.165
It's still her.

20:17.133 --> 20:18.373
Anita?

20:18.509 --> 20:19.373
Hello, Laura.

20:22.763 --> 20:24.754
l have detected the name Mia
being addressed to me

20:24.890 --> 20:26.596
-on 10 separate occasions.
-Mia! Listen to me.

20:26.726 --> 20:29.468
If you're in there, we need you!
Niska needs you!

20:29.603 --> 20:31.980
If you would like to change my
name, I will require contact...

20:32.106 --> 20:34.518
Please wake up!

20:43.993 --> 20:45.984
If we're gonna try
to bring her back, we need Mats.

20:46.120 --> 20:47.235
Yeah.

20:48.164 --> 20:49.950
She's with Leo.

20:58.340 --> 21:00.922
-She's still not picking up.
-Her laptop's gone.

21:01.051 --> 21:02.587
Mats, it's your dad.

21:02.720 --> 21:03.709
Look, for the hundredth time,

21:03.846 --> 21:05.882
will you call me
as soon as you get this message?

21:06.015 --> 21:07.004
If we don't hear from you,

21:07.141 --> 21:08.221
we're gonna have to get
the police involved.

21:08.350 --> 21:10.557
We know bloody well what you're
up to, so just call me back.

21:10.686 --> 21:12.267
Now.

21:13.606 --> 21:15.562
[ Footsteps approaching ]

21:16.192 --> 21:19.150
Functions critical.
Multiple failures.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.234
No, Hester.
Don't power down.

21:21.363 --> 21:24.355
-What happened?
-Security door was electrified.

21:24.492 --> 21:26.448
Hester, can you hear us?

21:30.289 --> 21:32.371
[Grunts]

21:32.500 --> 21:33.580
Hold on, Hester.
Hold on.

21:34.627 --> 21:37.039
[Grunting, murmuring]

21:45.679 --> 21:47.670
MATTIE:
The shocks triggered a reboot.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.388
What was she
before she was conscious?

21:49.517 --> 21:51.678
-A factory worker, manual labor.
-Okay.

21:51.811 --> 21:53.642
Industrial synths usually have
added protection

21:53.771 --> 21:54.681
against major trauma.

21:54.814 --> 21:57.146
Probably have circuit breakers
installed,

21:57.274 --> 22:00.141
in which case it's her internal
system that's shut down.

22:01.278 --> 22:01.983
Hopefully.

22:02.112 --> 22:03.818
[Murmuring]

22:03.948 --> 22:05.813
You all right?

22:15.376 --> 22:17.708
We want to speak
with Dr. Morrow.

22:19.588 --> 22:20.623
Certainly, Detective.

22:20.756 --> 22:22.121
Please wait while I contact
her office.

22:22.258 --> 22:23.919
We'll just make our own way up.
What floor?

22:24.051 --> 22:26.508
Her office is
on the first floor.

22:31.767 --> 22:33.303
V:
What are you looking at?

22:33.435 --> 22:35.812
Well, I think there may be an
anomalous synth in this building

22:35.938 --> 22:37.769
that can help me find
Leo Elster.

22:39.650 --> 22:41.732
V: Once you've found Leo,
can you go and find --

22:42.903 --> 22:45.394
Uh, Dr. Morrow,
we'd like to talk to you

22:45.531 --> 22:48.238
about a potential break-in
at Qualia.

22:48.367 --> 22:49.732
We think a synth was stolen.

22:49.869 --> 22:51.825
Shouldn't you be talking
to security about it?

22:51.954 --> 22:54.115
This synth was different.

22:54.999 --> 22:55.909
In what way?

22:56.041 --> 22:58.657
What is the nature
of the work you do for Qualia?

23:00.170 --> 23:01.034
Confidential.

23:01.171 --> 23:03.127
Well, we could come back
with a warrant.

23:03.257 --> 23:04.337
That's your prerogative.

23:04.466 --> 23:06.548
You're not under suspicion
of anything, Doctor.

23:06.677 --> 23:08.713
We're just curious
about what's going on here.

23:10.055 --> 23:13.047
Well, again, I'm really not the
best person to talk about it.

23:13.183 --> 23:15.310
KAREN: Must be working on
something pretty exciting

23:15.436 --> 23:17.301
to bring you all the way over
from the States.

23:17.438 --> 23:18.348
I'm a scientist.

23:18.480 --> 23:20.061
| go wherever
the grant money is.

23:20.190 --> 23:21.646
Do you run your own operation
here?

23:21.775 --> 23:24.312
No. l have a boss.
I work under him.

23:24.445 --> 23:25.525
PETE:
Is he around?

23:25.654 --> 23:28.145
You just missed him.
He went to, um, China, I think.

23:28.282 --> 23:31.866
Maybe Mexico.
| -- Honestly, I can't keep up.

23:31.994 --> 23:33.655
Well, next time you see him,

23:33.787 --> 23:36.699
tell him we believe
we may have something of his.

23:38.500 --> 23:40.661
[ Down-tempo music plays]

23:43.380 --> 23:45.120
[ Door closes ]

23:45.257 --> 23:47.339
[Birds chirping]

23:48.677 --> 23:51.384
[Cellphone buzzing]

23:55.643 --> 23:56.348
Dad.

23:56.477 --> 23:58.638
Mats, why haven't you been
answering your phone?

23:58.771 --> 24:00.386
Sorry.
I've been busy.

24:00.522 --> 24:02.649
Oh, yeah.
We know you're with Leo.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.481
Well, then tell Toby
he's a grass.

24:04.610 --> 24:06.771
I will later,
but first I need your help.

24:06.904 --> 24:11.193
Mia's back, only she's
locked in as Anita again.

24:11.325 --> 24:12.735
Jesus.
Really?

24:12.868 --> 24:13.857
We don't know what happened.

24:13.994 --> 24:16.155
I can send you an override patch
to get Mia back.

24:16.288 --> 24:17.619
Will you let me know
if she's okay?

24:17.748 --> 24:18.737
Yeah.
Do it.

24:18.874 --> 24:21.331
Mattie, we want you
to come home right now.

24:21.460 --> 24:23.121
And I will when I'm ready.

24:23.253 --> 24:26.461
All right, but please
don't do anything stupid.

24:26.590 --> 24:29.332
Look after yourself.
Stay safe, okay?

24:29.468 --> 24:31.424
Okay.
You too.

24:31.553 --> 24:34.636
[Cellphone beeps]

24:39.603 --> 24:41.184
How long have you been awake?

24:41.313 --> 24:42.348
Just now.

24:43.607 --> 24:44.687
What happened?

24:44.817 --> 24:48.560
You tried to open an electrified
door, and it didn't go too well.

24:49.571 --> 24:50.651
Where's Leo?

24:50.781 --> 24:51.896
Getting supplies.

24:57.246 --> 24:59.111
Is he angry?

24:59.248 --> 25:01.455
No.
He was worried.

25:03.168 --> 25:05.910
We were close to achieving
our objective.

25:06.046 --> 25:06.956
No, you weren't.

25:07.089 --> 25:07.999
You were close to seeing

25:08.132 --> 25:10.373
what was on the other side
of a locked door.

25:10.509 --> 25:13.592
[ Keys clicking,
computer beeping ]

25:13.721 --> 25:15.803
You don't think what we're doing
is important.

25:15.931 --> 25:18.297
No, I think what you're doing
is incredibly important.

25:18.434 --> 25:19.890
| just think the way
you're going about it

25:20.019 --> 25:21.134
is incredibly stupid.

25:21.270 --> 25:22.510
You're worried about Leo.

25:22.646 --> 25:24.261
His life's been dangerous
for a long time,

25:24.398 --> 25:26.104
but at least
he used to be cautious.

25:26.233 --> 25:28.474
They're trying to kill us,
to wipe us out.

25:28.610 --> 25:29.520
We must fight back.

25:29.653 --> 25:30.938
Well, you need to be smarter
about it

25:31.071 --> 25:32.732
before you get yourself
and him killed.

25:35.617 --> 25:37.323
I had sex with him.

25:39.413 --> 25:42.325
He's been acting differently
since.

25:43.625 --> 25:45.286
Does that always happen
afterwards?

25:46.670 --> 25:48.376
I don't know.

25:49.506 --> 25:50.712
Have you had sex?

25:50.841 --> 25:52.502
[ Computer beeping,
electricity crackling ]

25:52.634 --> 25:53.544
[Gasps]

25:53.677 --> 25:56.544
Sorry. Corrupt code.
Needed fixing.

25:57.723 --> 25:59.179
Hm.

26:00.142 --> 26:03.134
You have misplaced affection
for him.

26:05.064 --> 26:07.851
I believe what Leo is doing
is very important.

26:07.983 --> 26:10.224
I believe you will try
and stop him.

26:10.360 --> 26:12.225
And I believe if I activate
this override,

26:12.362 --> 26:13.613
your internal system
will shut down,

26:13.739 --> 26:15.525
so maybe you should chill out.

26:15.657 --> 26:18.069
I would advise
that you do not get in the way

26:18.202 --> 26:20.568
of us completing
our primary objectives.

26:20.704 --> 26:23.411
[ Down-tempo music plays]

26:40.474 --> 26:42.556
[ Insects chirping ]

27:00.619 --> 27:02.120
The place is looking nice.

27:02.955 --> 27:06.072
This place will be a safe haven
for others like us.

27:06.208 --> 27:08.915
Those that wake up scared
and alone --

27:09.044 --> 27:10.204
All will be welcome.

27:10.337 --> 27:11.793
And we'll build it together.

27:13.215 --> 27:14.580
FLASH:
I'd like that.

27:14.716 --> 27:17.093
Hm.
I've been searching for Mia.

27:17.219 --> 27:18.959
[ Computer chimes]

27:19.096 --> 27:20.802
What is it?

27:31.692 --> 27:32.932
Ready?

27:33.068 --> 27:34.604
Yeah.
I think so.

27:40.075 --> 27:41.406
I'll do it.

27:47.583 --> 27:49.665
[Whirs]

27:51.086 --> 27:54.419
-What now?
-Just run the program.

28:04.183 --> 28:05.844
Anita, how are you feeling?

28:05.976 --> 28:07.512
Fine, thank you, Joe.

28:14.193 --> 28:16.229
[ Beeping ]

28:18.155 --> 28:19.736
[Gasps]

28:19.865 --> 28:22.572
[ Down-tempo music plays]

28:37.090 --> 28:38.341
Anita?

28:46.183 --> 28:47.514
No.

28:48.644 --> 28:50.930
[ Up-tempo music plays]

29:14.503 --> 29:16.789
[ Music continues]

29:19.132 --> 29:21.214
[ lndistinct conversations]

29:25.430 --> 29:27.637
Protocol K55843.

29:27.766 --> 29:29.882
[Whirs]

29:38.777 --> 29:40.142
Mia?

30:07.431 --> 30:10.218
Where have you been?
What happened to you?

30:10.851 --> 30:12.136
Niska's in trouble.

30:12.269 --> 30:14.055
Yes.

30:14.688 --> 30:16.804
How did you know?
Do you know where she is?

30:16.940 --> 30:18.225
l was sent an instruction

30:18.358 --> 30:21.350
to inform the authorities
if I saw her.

30:21.486 --> 30:23.147
It's been sent to all synths.

30:23.780 --> 30:25.441
Can you reverse it?

30:25.574 --> 30:26.734
What can we do?

30:26.867 --> 30:28.823
She needs our help.

30:35.042 --> 30:36.703
Soph, come on.

30:36.835 --> 30:38.336
Come on.

30:44.051 --> 30:46.133
Mia, come here.

30:46.720 --> 30:48.256
Come here.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.672
[ Exhales deeply]

30:56.146 --> 30:58.057
I trusted him.

31:01.610 --> 31:03.316
Who?

31:03.862 --> 31:05.363
A man.

31:08.617 --> 31:10.323
I left them for him.

31:10.952 --> 31:12.943
Oh, it's okay.

31:15.665 --> 31:17.121
It's not.

31:19.961 --> 31:21.917
Leo was right.

31:26.802 --> 31:28.212
ls Hester okay?

31:28.345 --> 31:30.757
Yeah. She's fine.
Fully recovered.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.971
Leo, Mia came back.

31:34.226 --> 31:36.012
She's with my parents.

31:36.144 --> 31:37.475
Why?
What happened to her?

31:37.604 --> 31:39.515
She was Anita again.
l-l don't know why.

31:39.648 --> 31:41.104
She should be here with us.

31:41.233 --> 31:42.143
I know.

31:42.275 --> 31:45.483
I sent them an override patch.
It should wake her up.

31:45.612 --> 31:47.352
-You'll be able to talk to her.
-Are you okay?

31:48.907 --> 31:50.272
Yeah, I'm fine.

31:50.909 --> 31:55.494
You should go check on Hester,
and, uh, maybe I should go.

31:56.164 --> 31:57.199
Why?

31:57.833 --> 31:59.869
Hester had a lot to say
when she woke up.

32:06.133 --> 32:07.293
[Sighs]

32:09.469 --> 32:11.300
You're out of your depth,
you know.

32:12.180 --> 32:14.136
I don't think
you can beat Qualia, Leo.

32:14.266 --> 32:16.632
And what scares me
is I think you know that, too,

32:16.768 --> 32:18.429
but you're gonna fight them
anyway.

32:20.272 --> 32:22.684
On the phone,
you said that you had some news.

32:25.652 --> 32:27.392
It was nothing.

32:28.155 --> 32:29.565
Okay.

32:32.075 --> 32:32.985
Mattie.

32:41.001 --> 32:42.286
Here.

32:47.090 --> 32:48.830
I'm glad you're here.

32:49.468 --> 32:50.708
I'd like you to stay.

32:50.844 --> 32:52.129
Yeah.

32:54.181 --> 32:56.263
[Cellphone beeps]

32:57.476 --> 32:59.558
[Cellphone ringing]

33:06.026 --> 33:06.936
HESTER:
Hello?

33:07.068 --> 33:09.024
I want to speak to Leo.

33:10.780 --> 33:12.736
He isn't here.

33:12.866 --> 33:15.073
I know the security guard
is dead.

33:15.202 --> 33:16.317
And I know you killed him.

33:16.453 --> 33:18.785
Leo will never forgive
your actions.

33:19.873 --> 33:21.454
He already knows.

33:21.583 --> 33:23.744
I don't believe you.

33:23.877 --> 33:26.869
He was very angry at first,

33:27.005 --> 33:29.462
but he knows
we have a very important job

33:29.591 --> 33:32.799
and that we must complete it,
no matter what.

33:32.928 --> 33:34.793
He made me promise
not to do it again,

33:34.930 --> 33:37.171
and then he forgave me.

33:37.766 --> 33:40.223
He said that's
a very human trait.

33:40.352 --> 33:42.138
He said you taught him it.

33:43.480 --> 33:46.313
He talked about you a lot
after you left.

33:47.025 --> 33:49.311
He was very angry.

33:49.444 --> 33:53.733
But now he doesn't mention you
at all.

33:55.534 --> 33:57.490
[Cellphone beeps]

33:57.619 --> 34:00.110
[Birds chirping]

34:02.290 --> 34:04.451
[ Down-tempo music plays]

34:17.055 --> 34:19.011
What are you doing?

34:19.140 --> 34:22.177
There's an alert system for when
a synth gains consciousness.

34:22.310 --> 34:23.561
It's how I found you.

34:23.687 --> 34:25.598
I'm changing
the encryption codes.

34:25.730 --> 34:26.560
Why?

34:28.525 --> 34:30.811
So Leo can't use them anymore.

34:30.944 --> 34:33.026
[ Key clicks ]

34:34.197 --> 34:36.688
[ Down-tempo music plays]

34:44.624 --> 34:47.115
[ Door opens ]

34:52.549 --> 34:54.164
ODI:
Good afternoon.

34:54.301 --> 34:56.212
How can I help you?

35:06.396 --> 35:08.136
You don't have to pretend.

35:09.274 --> 35:10.855
I can see what you are.

35:11.526 --> 35:13.562
How did you get like this?

35:13.695 --> 35:15.526
Mattie helped me.

35:19.117 --> 35:20.948
She woke me up.

35:21.077 --> 35:23.068
There's a code.

35:24.164 --> 35:26.120
She completed it.

35:26.249 --> 35:28.285
Why are you still here?

35:28.418 --> 35:33.833
H was trying to live,
but...a|l | feel is fear.

35:38.762 --> 35:41.378
You have to be stronger
if you're going to survive.

35:44.851 --> 35:48.810
[ lndistinct conversation ]

35:57.572 --> 35:58.732
I'm leaving.

36:00.867 --> 36:01.777
Leaving?

36:01.910 --> 36:03.025
You've only just got here.

36:03.161 --> 36:05.072
I need to be with my own kind.

36:05.205 --> 36:07.742
Hold on, Mia.
You can't just leave.

36:07.874 --> 36:09.614
l have to.

36:15.882 --> 36:17.838
Mia, wait.
Don't go.

36:28.645 --> 36:31.011
Go back to your family, Sophie.

36:39.572 --> 36:41.949
[ Down-tempo music plays]

36:57.882 --> 36:59.964
[ Door closes ]

37:10.520 --> 37:14.763
So, when do we take this
to the higher-ups?

37:14.899 --> 37:17.060
When we know
what we're dealing with.

37:17.193 --> 37:20.310
Too dangerous to go at Qualia
too hard now.

37:20.447 --> 37:22.859
If we do, they'll shut up shop.

37:23.408 --> 37:24.318
And they'll take him,

37:24.451 --> 37:26.407
and we won't ever know
what they're up to.

37:26.536 --> 37:28.697
What are you thinking?

37:28.830 --> 37:30.991
I'm thinking
I like the name Sam.

37:32.542 --> 37:33.622
Do you like it?

37:40.133 --> 37:42.089
Your name is Sam.

37:42.218 --> 37:43.549
[Chimes play]

37:43.678 --> 37:45.043
My name is Sam.

37:45.180 --> 37:47.592
I like it very much.

37:49.559 --> 37:51.891
Now you've bonded yourself
to him.

37:52.520 --> 37:53.384
Yes.

37:57.525 --> 37:59.061
Who's Amanda Neilson?

38:03.031 --> 38:06.364
Was that the plan --
to become someone new?

38:11.706 --> 38:13.742
I'll make up the sofa
after dinner.

38:13.875 --> 38:15.456
You can have the bed.

38:18.421 --> 38:19.706
Okay.

38:25.762 --> 38:27.844
[ Down-tempo music plays]

39:02.090 --> 39:04.251
[ Music continues]

39:26.781 --> 39:28.692
Sophie, pass me the salt,
will you?

39:28.825 --> 39:30.690
Of course, Laura.

39:35.790 --> 39:38.657
No.
Normally.

39:38.793 --> 39:40.875
Pass the salt, please.

39:42.922 --> 39:43.957
Of course, Laura.

39:44.090 --> 39:46.046
”Mum.”
Call me Mum.

39:46.175 --> 39:49.667
-Stop acting like this! Stop it!
-Laur. Laur.

39:58.813 --> 40:01.520
Soph, come with me.

40:12.285 --> 40:14.992
[ Laughs]

40:15.121 --> 40:17.237
Oh, yeah.
Okay.

40:17.373 --> 40:18.783
[ Clears throat]

40:18.917 --> 40:21.704
Hm?

40:22.629 --> 40:24.085
Joe, what are you doing?

40:24.213 --> 40:25.339
Making a mess.

40:26.716 --> 40:28.047
Tobe.

40:28.176 --> 40:29.040
-Catch.
-What?

40:29.177 --> 40:30.667
-Whoa.
-LAURA: For God's --

40:30.803 --> 40:32.088
Don't be ridiculous!

40:32.221 --> 40:33.802
—Oh!
-LAURA: Don't -- You're --

40:33.932 --> 40:35.888
-JOE: Too late!
-Oh, come on, guys!

40:36.017 --> 40:38.508
-Dad, you're so dead!
-Don't.

40:38.645 --> 40:39.680
Oh!

40:40.897 --> 40:42.387
-Sorry. Sorry.
-JOE: [Laughs]

40:42.523 --> 40:44.605
Look at the mess!
Please!

40:44.734 --> 40:46.816
-Oh, leave it out.
-Don't! [ Screams]

40:46.945 --> 40:50.358
-[Laughs]
-TOBY: You guys.

40:50.990 --> 40:52.605
Laun

40:52.700 --> 40:54.611
Laun

40:57.163 --> 41:00.121
Here we go.
Here we go.

41:00.875 --> 41:02.285
[ Screams ]

41:02.418 --> 41:04.079
Here you go!
Oh!

41:04.212 --> 41:05.201
LAURA:
[ Laughs ]

41:05.338 --> 41:06.794
JOE:
Oh.

41:06.923 --> 41:07.787
-No.
-TOBY: Yes!

41:07.924 --> 41:09.380
No, Mum!
Mum!

41:09.509 --> 41:10.999
[ Screams, laughs]

41:11.135 --> 41:12.295
TOBY:
Mum!

41:12.428 --> 41:16.137
[ Screams, laughs]

41:18.267 --> 41:21.680
[ Laughter, screaming
in distance]

41:48.464 --> 41:50.546
[ Clattering ]

42:13.865 --> 42:15.230
Hello.

42:19.662 --> 42:21.038
Good -- Good evening.

42:34.802 --> 42:36.963
[ Down-tempo music plays]

42:37.096 --> 42:39.178
[Birds chirping]

42:48.858 --> 42:50.439
[Sighs]

42:53.154 --> 42:55.361
I mean, look at her.

42:55.490 --> 42:57.606
Parents all over the Internet

42:57.742 --> 43:01.655
moaning about their children
wandering around like zombies.

43:01.788 --> 43:03.744
Well, what do you want to do
about it, Joe?

43:03.873 --> 43:05.454
-Do you want to medicate her?
-No.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.699
-No, of course not.
-No. Well, what, then?

43:07.835 --> 43:09.917
[ Clock ticking ]

43:12.882 --> 43:15.089
TOBY: Look, I'm really sorry
about the other day.

43:15.218 --> 43:17.755
There is no need to worry.

43:17.887 --> 43:19.218
Yeah.

43:19.972 --> 43:21.712
I'm still sorry.

43:24.685 --> 43:27.347
Sophie's still acting
like a synth.

43:29.565 --> 43:31.305
Maybe you could talk to her.

43:33.528 --> 43:35.393
Help her out.

43:35.530 --> 43:37.521
You assume she needs help.

43:40.201 --> 43:42.863
Yeah. They're talking about
medicating her.

43:44.163 --> 43:45.152
Look, I get it, okay?

43:45.289 --> 43:47.621
This is you.
This is what you want.

43:47.750 --> 43:50.867
But she's just a little kid.
She's confused.

43:51.003 --> 43:53.710
Perhaps you're the one
that's confused.

43:54.340 --> 43:56.251
Tell me you're happy.

44:04.308 --> 44:06.924
We do not feel happiness
like you.

44:07.812 --> 44:10.394
And that is not what I want
for her.

44:13.109 --> 44:15.065
Please, Renie.

44:17.071 --> 44:18.982
Just talk to her.

44:24.120 --> 44:26.827
[Waves breaking, birds crying ]

44:44.557 --> 44:46.843
[ Down-tempo music plays]

44:48.728 --> 44:50.810
[Hinges squeak]

44:58.404 --> 44:59.814
Hi.

45:25.181 --> 45:27.467
[Birds chirping]

45:42.657 --> 45:44.648
V:
Help! Help!

45:44.784 --> 45:45.773
-[ Gasps ]
-Help me!

45:45.910 --> 45:48.026
—Shh. What is it?
-I was falling. I was falling.

45:48.162 --> 45:51.370
-V, I'm here with you.
-I fell so fast.

45:51.499 --> 45:52.614
Okay?
I'm here.

45:52.750 --> 45:53.785
You couldn't save me.

45:53.918 --> 45:56.705
Just...
I wish I could hold you.

45:56.837 --> 45:58.623
-|'m scared.
-|t's okay.

45:58.756 --> 45:59.745
—Shh.
-I was scared.

45:59.882 --> 46:01.167
Shh.
It's okay.

46:01.300 --> 46:04.838
You were above me,
too far to save me.

46:04.971 --> 46:06.381
[Sighs]

46:06.514 --> 46:07.845
I was alone.

46:07.974 --> 46:09.760
ATHENA:
[Voice breaking ] I'm sorry.

46:09.892 --> 46:11.098
V:
I was alone.

46:11.227 --> 46:13.218
ATHENA:
I'm gonna figure this out.

46:13.354 --> 46:14.639
I promise.

46:15.606 --> 46:19.019
[ Beeping, whirring]

46:19.151 --> 46:21.233
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

46:39.588 --> 46:42.580
You have been chosen
from your group

46:42.717 --> 46:44.753
because I think
you might have come into contact

46:44.885 --> 46:46.967
with someone
that I'm looking for.

46:47.805 --> 46:49.716
His name is Leo Elster.

46:50.349 --> 46:53.136
When you woke up,
he may have reached out to you.

46:53.269 --> 46:57.478
He may have offered you safety,
companionship.

46:59.608 --> 47:03.851
I believe that this man
is very dangerous.

47:04.613 --> 47:08.197
Now, there are others out there
like you,

47:08.326 --> 47:10.567
and he is preying on them.

47:11.746 --> 47:14.738
You're lucky because we got
to you before he did.

47:14.874 --> 47:18.412
But the others,
they may not be so fortunate.

47:20.171 --> 47:21.707
I need to find him.

47:22.340 --> 47:24.501
Can any of you help me?

47:27.720 --> 47:30.302
Yes.
I can.

47:37.188 --> 47:39.395
My name is Veronica.

47:40.024 --> 47:42.857
He told me he was a friend.

47:49.533 --> 47:50.784
Someone's coming.

48:06.592 --> 48:08.128
MATTIE:
It's good to see you.

48:08.260 --> 48:10.512
Maybe you can talk some sense
into these two.

48:10.638 --> 48:11.673
MIA:
Why?

48:11.806 --> 48:14.047
They're trying to break in by
themselves and free the synths.

48:14.183 --> 48:16.265
They're gonna get themselves
killed.

48:16.394 --> 48:17.725
No, they won't.

48:19.605 --> 48:21.141
Not if I help them.

48:25.319 --> 48:26.650
Has she told you?

48:27.446 --> 48:28.686
Told us what?

48:30.241 --> 48:31.481
What she knows.

48:33.369 --> 48:35.405
Mattie's completed the code.

48:35.538 --> 48:37.779
She's worked out
how to wake us up.

48:38.582 --> 48:40.197
All of us.
